Shapes $1$, $2$ and $3$ of a growing pattern of dots are shown. Which equation gives the number of dots $y$ in shape $x$?
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}
\fill (0,0) circle (0.08);
\fill (0,0.5) circle (0.08);
\fill (0,1) circle (0.08);
\node at (0,-0.55) {$1$};
\fill (1.5,0) circle (0.08);
\fill (1.5,0.5) circle (0.08);
\fill (1.5,1) circle (0.08);
\fill (2,0) circle (0.08);
\fill (2,0.5) circle (0.08);
\fill (2,1) circle (0.08);
\node at (1.75,-0.55) {$2$};
\fill (3.5,0) circle (0.08);
\fill (3.5,0.5) circle (0.08);
\fill (3.5,1) circle (0.08);
\fill (4,0) circle (0.08);
\fill (4,0.5) circle (0.08);
\fill (4,1) circle (0.08);
\fill (4.5,0) circle (0.08);
\fill (4.5,0.5) circle (0.08);
\fill (4.5,1) circle (0.08);
\node at (4,-0.55) {$3$};
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]

This matchstick pattern grows by adding triangles. Which equation gives the number of matches $y$ in shape $x$?
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.9]
\draw[thick] (0,0)--(1,0);
\draw[thick] (0,0)--(0.5,0.8);
\draw[thick] (1,0)--(0.5,0.8);
\fill (0,0) circle (0.05);
\fill (1,0) circle (0.05);
\fill (0.5,0.8) circle (0.05);
\node at (0.5,-0.4) {$1$};
\draw[thick] (2.2,0)--(3.2,0);
\draw[thick] (2.2,0)--(2.7,0.8);
\draw[thick] (3.2,0)--(2.7,0.8);
\draw[thick] (2.7,0.8)--(3.7,0.8);
\draw[thick] (3.2,0)--(3.7,0.8);
\fill (2.2,0) circle (0.05);
\fill (3.2,0) circle (0.05);
\fill (2.7,0.8) circle (0.05);
\fill (3.7,0.8) circle (0.05);
\node at (2.95,-0.4) {$2$};
\draw[thick] (4.9,0)--(5.9,0);
\draw[thick] (5.9,0)--(6.9,0);
\draw[thick] (4.9,0)--(5.4,0.8);
\draw[thick] (5.9,0)--(5.4,0.8);
\draw[thick] (5.4,0.8)--(6.4,0.8);
\draw[thick] (5.9,0)--(6.4,0.8);
\draw[thick] (6.9,0)--(6.4,0.8);
\fill (4.9,0) circle (0.05);
\fill (5.9,0) circle (0.05);
\fill (6.9,0) circle (0.05);
\fill (5.4,0.8) circle (0.05);
\fill (6.4,0.8) circle (0.05);
\node at (5.9,-0.4) {$3$};
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]
